solution.p:
We substitute a = 1, b =-2, and c= 2 into the quadratic formula to get
		x=\frac{-(-2)\pm\sqrt{(-2)^2-4(1)(2)}}{2(1)}=\frac{2\pm\sqrt{-4}}{2}
Because \sqrt{-4} is not a real number, the equation x^2 - 2x + 2 = 0 has no real solutions.

